- Pure numeric: r"^\s*\d+(?:.\d+)?\s*$"
- Standalone dosage-form words (already stripped upstream by
_DOSAGE_QUALIFIERS regex)

Additionally strip trailing dose strings BEFORE splitting:
Apply r"\s*\d+(?:.\d+)?\smg\s/\s*\d+(?:.\d+)?\smg\b" removal to the
product name so "5mg/120mg" is gone before any "and" split.

