RED FLAG 3 — STP test extractor over-flattens hierarchy
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Symptom: Section 8.2 Pseudoephedrine spec shows 42 tests when the approved
document lists 6-7. Extractor treats microbiology sub-tests, confirmation
tests, and pathogen sub-tests as separate top-level line items.
Example bloat:
27. Microbiological Test
28. Microbial Enumeration Test
29. TYMC
30. TAMC
31. Pathogen Analysis
32. Staphylococcus aureus
33. Confirmation test: Gram staining
... (through 42)

Root cause: STP converter emits every test method row as a separate item
with no hierarchy collapse.

Fix in benoc_annexure_convertor.py STP extractor:
1. Post-process tests_covered[] to collapse child tests under a parent when
the parent test name is a category keyword:
Category patterns:
- "microbiological test" / "microbial enumeration" / "microbial limits"
→ merge all TYMC / TAMC / Pathogen / individual organism entries
under a single "Microbiological Testing" line
- "identification" (top-level) + "identification by IR/UV/HPLC" (child)
→ keep parent, drop children OR merge as sub-labels
- "confirmation test" → merge under parent test being confirmed
- "growth in TSI Agar", "Indole test", "Catalase test", "Oxidase test",
"Gram staining" → subordinate to nearest parent (pathogen category)
2. When extractor encounters a pathogen category ("Salmonella",
"E.coli", "Clostridia", "Candida albicans", "Staphylococcus aureus"),
collapse it and all its confirmation sub-tests under
"Pathogen Analysis".
3. Emit maximum 15 top-level tests per STP even for comprehensive STPs.
4. Preserve full hierarchy in an internal _tests_detail field for audit
but the tests_covered[] list used by build_specs_from_stp() is the
collapsed list.

