RED FLAG 4 — Storage condition label contamination in stability blocks
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Symptom: Section 13 and annexure list show all stability blocks labeled
"25°C/60%RH" even when file is a 40°C/75%RH file. The wrong condition is
in the storage_condition field; the true condition only appears in the
table's column header ("Stability- 40°C/75%RH").

Root cause: stability file extractor is reading storage_condition from the
wrong location (probably the column header for the first stability column,
which contains the initial condition, not from the top-of-document
condition declaration).

Fix in benoc_annexure_convertor.py stability extractor:
1. Extract storage_condition from the top-of-document header line
(usually "Storage Condition: 40°C/75%RH" or from the file's title
line "F-NB1-80 4075" filename pattern).
2. Do NOT extract storage_condition from column headers of the result
table. Column headers contain timepoints ("Initial", "1M", "6M"),
not storage conditions.
3. Filter timepoint values to reject strings that look like conditions:
- Reject if matches r"stability\s[-—]\s*\d+"
- Reject if matches r"\d+°?[CF]\s*/\s*\d+%\sRH?"
- Reject if starts with "Stability-" or "Stability -"
4. If storage_condition cannot be extracted from body, infer from filename:
"F-NB1-80 2560" → "25°C/60%RH"
"F-NB1-80 4075" → "40°C/75%RH"
Store as _condition_source: "filename_inferred".

Fix in benoc.py build_stability_sources():
Filter timepoints defensively before building the annexure title:
clean_tps = [t for t in raw_tps
if t and not t.lower().startswith("stability-")
and not t.lower().startswith("stability -")
and not re.match(r"\d+°?[cf]\s/\s*\d+%?", t.lower())
and t.lower() not in ("stability", "condition", "storage")]

Acceptance:
