PER-DOC-TYPE MERGE FUNCTIONS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Each doc type has one merge function that extracts doc-relevant fields from
a cluster. Add to the doc type's backend module.

DEG/EG (deg_eg.py):
def merge_deg_eg_evidence(cluster) -> Dict:
Extract from all cluster annexures:
- material_code (via _pick_best_material_code)
- vendor / manufacturer_name (via _pick_best_vendor)
- drl_specification_no (via _pick_best_specification_no)
- deg_present: prefer Yes (batch-tested) > No (guarantee ceiling) > No (default)
- eg_present: same priority
- deg_specification_limit / eg_specification_limit: first non-null
- fda_high_risk: True if any annexure sets it (or material canonical is on
FDA high-risk list: glycerin, propylene glycol, sorbitol, mannitol,
maltitol, HSH, PEG, polysorbate)
- mechanism: extracted from pooled raw_text (hydrogenation by-product,
manufacturing residue, etc.)
- guarantee_ceiling: True if pooled raw_text contains guarantee-ceiling
signals (see prior DEG/EG spec)

Downgrade rules (preserve prior Tier 1/2/3 fixes):
- Yes + guarantee-ceiling signals → downgrade to No, keep spec_limit
- Yes + policy_statement source → downgrade to Unknown then No
- Yes + no numeric limit → downgrade to Unknown then No

RESIDUAL SOLVENT (residual_solvent.py):
def merge_rs_evidence(cluster) -> Dict:
Extract from all cluster annexures:
- material_name, material_code, supplier, drl_spec_no
- solvents[]: union of all solvent entries across cluster
- Deduplicate by (canonical_solvent, compendial_priority) using existing
dedup logic in process_rs_annexure
- Apply NMT-over-batch-actual preference (existing rule)
- Apply USP/NF-first compendial preference (existing rule)
- negative_declaration: True if ANY cluster annexure has it AND
no positive solvent entries exist (respect the "if solvents[] has any
positive limit → false" rule from prior fix)
- declaration_scopes: union across cluster

BE NOC (benoc.py):
def merge_benoc_evidence(cluster) -> Dict:
Extract from all cluster annexures based on annexure_type:
For api_information cluster:
- iupac_name, molecular_formula, molecular_weight, cas_number,
therapeutic_category, indications, manufacturer, manufacturer_address,
smiles → first non-empty from cluster, prefer CoA over SDS over DMF
For stability_file cluster: not typically clustered (each timepoint unique)
For stp_document cluster: not typically clustered (drug substance vs FP distinct)
For manufacturing_license cluster: cluster only if same license_number
(different Form 25 numbers = different clusters)

ELEMENTAL IMPURITY (annexure_converter.py / EI backend):
def merge_ei_evidence(cluster) -> Dict:
Extract from all cluster annexures:
- material_name, material_code, supplier
- elements[]: union across cluster, deduplicate by (symbol, source_priority)
- Prefer measured concentration values over LOD/LOQ statements
- Apply existing EI evidence-priority logic
- source_type: pick most authoritative (CoA > vendor decl > MSDS)

